These are essential works that will improve the reliability of the electricity network, ensure the quality of supply in your area and will also reduce the risk of you having an unplanned power cut which. This is why it is important to complete this work during the Coronavirus pandemic. This work is taking place in the Tompsets Bank and Balfour Gardens area. A third party has requested that UK Power Networks switch off the power to allow them to carry out tree trimming safely around our overhead electricity cables. When the third party has completed their works our engineers will be able to restore power. This work will ensure that the trees are trimmed to their satisfaction and are not close to our overhead electricity cables. This will also reduce the possibility of you having an unplanned power cut by stopping these trees from potentially causing damage to our overhead electricity network. This work is taking place on Spithurst Road. The government has given exemptions to certain industries and activities, this outage falls into this category.

Following a third party request we are upgrading the electricity supply as part of improvement works for one of their sites. While the power is switched off our engineers are going to take the opportunity to replace two high voltage electricity poles that have come to end of their serviceable lives. Doing this work at the same time will hopefully minimise any disruption in the future, improve the reliability of the electricity network along with reducing the risk of you having an unplanned power cut. This is why its important to complete this work durimng the coronavirus pandemic. This work is taking place at a site off Newick Hill and Fletching Mill. The government has given exemptions to certain industries and activities, this outage falls into this category.

There is an unplanned power cut affecting the CH48 postcode area of Wirral, affecting properties in Column Road, Column Road West, Grange Cross Lane and surrounding streets. It will be necessary for our engineers to carry out an emergency shutdown at 11.15am to safely continue repairs on an underground cable fault. Our team will be carrying out repair work safely on the underground cable network and this may affect the supply to your property. We will work to get your power back on as quickly and as safely as possible, and we expect the power to be restored by 4.00pm. We will update this message if this information changes. We apologise for the inconvenience and thank you for your patience. This message was updated at 10.34am on 13th April 2021.
